    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>white long grain rice</strong>, a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]<strong> </span>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, add the <strong>blanched peas</strong>, remove from the heat and keep covered until the peas are warmed through</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
